definitions.definition: The state or condition of being complete .

The property of a logical theory that whenever a wff is valid then it must also be a theorem . Symbolically, letting T represent a theory within logic L , this can be represented as the property that whenever T ⊨ ϕ {\displaystyle T\vDash \phi } is true, then T ⊢ ϕ {\displaystyle T\vdash \phi } must also be true, for any wff φ of logic L .

main_definition: The state or condition of being complete .
